metadata.name: fxTesla #13
metadata.description:
Today, I`m going to introduce you to another personality. Moreover, this idol from previous collection had a great influence on me.

Nikola Tesla is a creator and genius whose vision of the world is clearly ahead of his time and biography inspires modern minds to create.
 
The modern world is hash and pragmatic, science has become commonplace and boring. With few exceptions, we learn about new inventions immediately from the «counters». They satisfy the usual needs of society, making our life easier.

Nikola Tesla showed the world the beauty of physics. I wonder what contribution he could have made to modern science?

KRCHR ©

Self-taught artist. I love physics and mathematics. I love the world around me. I love studying it.

metadata.name: Lines and reflections, burn. #9
metadata.description:
The repetitions of the lines form the sequence, the refraction of the lines in polarization angles is generated through repetitions of the lines and divisions of the Brewster angles, but the light here is not emitted from a single point of reference, the light and shadow is a result of the accumulation of lines in a point of polar refraction, where the oscillators indicate the object its changes, the repeated triangles are images of the first reflection, those with larger numbers are successive reflections.

Hydra/javascript on hash, highly. Marcelo Moura

metadata.name: Elswhere #67
metadata.description:
Perlin noise walks into a Julia set and finds itself Elswhere. X is real, Y is imaginary, or is it the other way around? 

Elswhere is a unique generative art series in which noise and fractal math are combined to create whimsical shapes and motifs, with an infinite number of variations. Made with p5js.

For each pixel, the noise values corresponding to the X and Y coordinates are computed and then used as the real and imaginary components for initializing a Julia set recursion. The pixel is colored based on the number of steps it takes for the recursion to reach its base case.

Keyboard controls:
[S] Save the current view.
[2] Render 2000x3000px image.
[4] Render 4000x6000px image.
[6] Render 6000x9000px image.

Created by Elsif, 2022.05

metadata.name: Flow #254
metadata.description:
Flow is a collection of eye pleasing formula's in the form of patterns and colors.

Features include:
- Patterns
- Palettes
- Focus points
- Margins
- Sizes
- Spacings
- Color distribution patterns
- Modifiers
- Gradients
- Dots
- Overflow

Due to the large amount of calculations it may take a few seconds to generate.
The spinning indicator on the top right disappears when it is finished, this is the best moment to save.

Press [s] to save a high resolution PNG @ 9933x14043 pixels (A0 paper dimensions @ 300 DPI).

Flow By @OneDayOfCrypto, 2022
